Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and chopped into small pieces) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{2}, then slice lengthways into ½cm strips. Chop the @cherry plum tomatoes{100}(in half) in half. Pick the @basil{12}(leaves picked from stalks, discard the stalks). Cut three-quarters of the @mozzarella{1}(three-quarters cut into thin slices) cheese into thin slices. Pat the slices with some #kitchen paper{} to soak up as much moisture as possible.

Put a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-low heat. Add the onion and garlic. Fry, stirring occasionally, until soft, about ~{5%minutes}. Add the @tomato passata{1} and @dried oregano{1/2}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Let the mixture simmer for ~{5%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in another frying pan on high heat. Once hot, fry the courgette strips in batches. Cook them for ~{1%minute} on each side, then set aside.

> TIP: Don't overcrowd the pan as this will stew the courgette rather than brown it nicely.

Put a third of the passata in an #ovenproof dish{} and spread it out to cover the bottom. Top this with a layer of courgette (use roughly half your courgette here as you're going to repeat this step). Next layer on half the sliced mozzarella. Tear over a third of your basil leaves and add half the @pine nuts{25}.

Spread on another layer of passata, followed by the remaining courgette, sliced mozzarella and pine nuts. Tear on another third of the basil. Finish with a final layer of passata and top your parmigiana with the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and @panko breadcrumbs{19.8%g}. Pop on the top shelf of your oven and bake for ~{15%minutes}. Slice the @ciabatta{1} in half and drizzle a dash of @oil{} on top. When the parmigiana has 5 mins left to cook, warm the ciabatta in the oven on a #baking tray{}.

Tear up the remaining basil and mozzarella. Put in a #mixing bowl{} with the cherry tomatoes. Add a drizzle of @olive oil{} and season with salt and pepper. When the parmigiana is ready, serve generous portions with the salad and ciabatta on the side. Enjoy!